# CODEOWNERS — trust-critical paths for credential-badges.
#
# DOCUMENT-ONLY gate (v1). This file records who must review changes to the
# paths below. It is intentionally NOT yet backed by branch-protection
# required-reviewers — a named team with >=2 required reviewers is deferred to
# productionization (deployment plan P1bis-09; "v1 has James as owner"). The
# cheap companion control is disabling force-push to the default branch.
#
# Scoped to Rungs 3-4 (did:web resolves; issuer Profile = AttestationHost).
# Later rungs extend this to the status-list JSON and tools/flip-status-bit.ts
# (Rung 8).

# The did:web DID document and its deterministic regenerator — this publishes
# the issuer signing key. A wrong or drifted key here silently breaks OB 3.0
# verification for every credential, so changes get a deliberate review. The
# whole /.well-known/** is gated (not just did.json) so any future sibling
# served on this forever-public path is reviewed too. did-pin.test.ts holds the
# pinned key constant (the actual invariant), so it is gated alongside.
/.well-known/**                @workshop-maybe
/tools/gen-did-json.ts         @workshop-maybe
/tools/did-pin.test.ts         @workshop-maybe

# The hosted OB 3.0 issuer Profile and the served JSON-LD context (Rung 4). The
# Profile declares the issuer as ["Profile","AttestationHost"] and names the
# did:web subject; the context DEFINES the AttestationHost extension term the
# Profile references. A wrong id, a dropped type, or an undefined term silently
# breaks strict-verifier expansion for every credential, so changes get a
# deliberate review. tools/issuer-profile.test.ts pins the shape invariant, so
# it is gated alongside.
/issuer/profile.jsonld         @workshop-maybe
/context/v0.jsonld             @workshop-maybe
/tools/issuer-profile.test.ts  @workshop-maybe

# Served-file allowlist controls. Adding a public, forever-served path must be
# a deliberate reviewed act — these four files are the allowlist surface
# (Dockerfile COPY, build-context re-includes, nginx location, CI gate).
/Dockerfile                    @workshop-maybe
/.dockerignore                 @workshop-maybe
/nginx/default.conf.template   @workshop-maybe
/scripts/ci/check-allowlist.sh @workshop-maybe
